What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Genetic Disorders Market?

Market Analysis and Size

The incidence of genetic disorders such as Down syndrome is caused by an extra copy of chromosome 21, and occurs in approximately 1 in 700 live births in the United States, Sickle cell anemia, is caused by a mutation in the HBB gene, affects approximately 1 in 365 African Americans and Cystic Fibrosis, is caused by mutations in the CFTR gene, affects approximately 1 in 2,500 to 3,500 Caucasian new-borns every year.

